ratings.comment: Problem sets posted 2 days before exam, exam questions not really reflective of lecture. Good guy though

Doesn't know how to prioritize lecture. Difficult mechanisms were introduced in the last 3 minutes of the class before tests, while spending days on easy concepts. Not clear with material, lecture offers no additional understanding. If you take him, be ready for hours searching for youtube reaction videos and reading the book for tests.

Helpful in office hours. Lots of resources available but not uploaded with enough time in advance to utilize. Lecture was straight from the book but crammed the important material and droned about concepts that were not applicable. Exams will blindside you if you don't know the book and even the expectations from the book are vague

Very slow paced lecturer, but fast paced when he needs to cram some more material before exam, and if he can't cram some more stuff before exam, he'll tell you to read the book (-_-)... He's very nice and approachable though. STUDY AHEAD OF TIME!!! Chem 345 is no joke. A LOT OF MATERIAL! Try to get ahead of lectures. Practice!
Very slow lecturer. He accomplished what my professor last semester would accomplish in 15 minutes in each 50 minute lecture. He has a very generous curve on his tests, which can be difficult.
Easy exams with a lot of resources. Very helpful during office hour. Cute in a grandfather way. Must take O-chem with this guy.
This professor is probably the best professor I have ever had in 2 years of my college experience. Take him and see what happens.
just ROCKED the final exam. Whooot!!!!!
UW madison really knows how to hire good professors.
He was overall a very pleasant professor. I would highly recommend.
horrible lectures but easy tests and quizes read the book and go to discussion
Organic chem is really hard but he makes it doable. He is a very attractive man as well..
I was going to do pre-med but decided to major in O-chem after this class. That said, I LOVE FRAZEE <3

He is a new professor and I was a bit worried about having him for O-chem, but he has been SUCH AN AMAZING EXPERIENCE. He KNOWS his chemistry and very passionate about his subject O-Chem. I would highly recommend him!!
Seriously, he is the man for O Chem. Very easy exams & quizzes. You just have to go to the lecture to take some notes. Highly recommend.
BEST professor I ever had in my life.
